\sum_{k=1}^n\frac{1}{\sqrt{k}+\sqrt{k+1}}
 \frac{1}{\sqrt{k}+\sqrt{k+1}} = \frac{-\sqrt{k}+\sqrt{k+1}}{(k+1) - (k)}  = -\sqrt{k}+\sqrt{k+1} 
 \sum_{k = 1}^N  \frac{1}{\sqrt{k}+\sqrt{k+1}} = \sum_{k = 1}^N -\sqrt{k}+\sqrt{k+1} = -1 + \sqrt{N+1} \to \infty 
\frac1{\sqrt k+\sqrt{k+1}}\ge\frac1{2\sqrt{k+1}}
